    think='We have read the main files. Now let\'s plan the fixes.\n\nReview iss
ues:\n\n**Blocking #1**: `_onConversationUpdated` only dispatches `LoadConversat
ions` if `state is ConversationListLoaded`, but `MatchListPage` never sends `Loa
dConversations` to `ImBloc`, it uses `ConversationListCubit`. So `ImBloc` state 
never becomes `ConversationListLoaded`. Fix: remove the state type check in `_on
ConversationUpdated` and always `add(const LoadConversations())`. Also add `cont
ext.read<ImBloc>().add(const LoadConversations())` in `MatchListPage.initState` 
to get initial state into `ConversationListLoaded`, so the `BlocListener` listen
When can hit. Wait: `BlocListener` listens to `ImBloc`, and its `listenWhen` ret
urns true when `current is ConversationListLoaded`. If we add `LoadConversations
()` in `initState`, then the state becomes `ConversationListLoaded`. Then when a
`ConversationUpdated` arrives, `_onConversationUpdated` adds another `LoadConver
sations`, which emits a new `ConversationListLoaded`, triggering the listener. T
hat should work.\n\nBut note: `MatchListPage` has a `BlocListener<ImBloc, ImStat
e>`. If we add `LoadConversations` to `ImBloc` in `initState`, the listener will
be triggered and call `ConversationListCubit.fetchConversations()`. That is okay
. So we need to add `context.read<ImBloc>().add(const LoadConversations());` in 
`MatchListPage.initState`.\n\n**Major #2**: `_pendingMessages` has no cache limi
t. Need to add `_maxPendingMessages = 500` and `_enforcePendingCacheLimit()` tha
t does global FIFO removal across conversations. Call it in `_onReceiveMessage` 
when message is added to pending (the else branch where conversationId != curren
t). We also need to consider per-conversation limit but the review suggests glob
al 500 is fine.\n\n**Major #3**: Socket disconnect/reconnect callbacks missing. 
Need to:\n- Add `onConnect`, `onDisconnect`, `onReconnectError` callbacks to `Im
SocketClient`.\n- Register socket events for `connect`, `disconnect`, `reconnect
_error`.\n- Add new events `ImSocketConnected`, `ImSocketDisconnected` to `im_ev
ent.dart`.\n- Add handlers `_onSocketConnected`, `_onSocketDisconnected` in `ImB
loc` to update `isConnected` in state (when state is MessagesLoaded).\n- In `_on
ImDisconnectRequested` or `onDisconnect` handler, if current state is `MessageSe
nding`, degrade `sending` messages to `failed` and emit `MessagesLoaded` with `i
sConnected: false`.\n\nWait: The review says:\n1. Add connection state callbacks
to `ImSocketClient`.\n2. Add `ImSocketConnected` / `ImSocketDisconnected` Event 
in `ImBloc` and update `isConnected`.\n3. In `_onImDisconnectRequested` or `onDi
sconnect` handler, if current state is `MessageSending`, degrade to `failed`.\n\
nBut note: `_onImDisconnectRequested` is called when user explicitly disconnects
(e.g., logout). The review also says `ImSocketClient` should register `onDisconn
ect` / `onReconnectError`. If socket disconnects unexpectedly, `ImBloc` should g
et `ImSocketDisconnected`. In that handler, we should also degrade `MessageSendi
ng` to `failed`.\n\nLet\'s implement:\n- In `ImSocketClient`, add `final void Fu
nction()? onConnect; final void Function()? onDisconnect; final void Function(in
t attempt)? onReconnectError;`.\n- In `connect()`, register `_socket?.on(\'conne
ct\', ...)` calling `onConnect?.()`, `_socket?.on(\'disconnect\', ...)` calling 
`onDisconnect?.()`, `_socket?.on(\'reconnect_error\', ...)` calling `onReconnect
Error?.(attempt)`.\n- In `ImBloc._onImConnectRequested`, pass these callbacks wh
en constructing `ImSocketClient`:\n  - `onConnect: () => add(const ImSocketConne
cted())`\n  - `onDisconnect: () => add(const ImSocketDisconnected())`\n  - `onRe
connectError: (_) => add(const ImSocketDisconnected())` (simpler).\n- Add events
`ImSocketConnected`, `ImSocketDisconnected` in `im_event.dart`.\n- Add handlers 
in `ImBloc`:\n  - `_onSocketConnected`: if state is MessagesLoaded, emit with `i
sConnected: true`.\n  - `_onSocketDisconnected`: handle degrade:\n    ```dart\n 
  if (state is MessageSending) {\n      final msgs = (state as MessageSending).m
essages.map((m) => m.status == \'sending\' ? m.copyWith(status: \'failed\') : m)
.toList();\n      emit(MessagesLoaded(messages: msgs, hasMore: false, isConnecte
d: false));\n    } else if (state is MessagesLoaded) {\n      emit(MessagesLoade
d(messages: (state as MessagesLoaded).messages, hasMore: (state as MessagesLoade
d).hasMore, nextCursor: ..., isConnected: false, ...));\n    }\n    ```\nBut als
o need to keep other fields like `lastReadMessageId` etc.\n\nWe also need to upd
ate `_onSendMessage`: currently when socket not connected, it sets status to fai
led. That\'s okay. But if socket disconnects after send, we need the disconnect 
handler to degrade.\n\n**Major #4**: BLoC unit test missing `MessageAckReceived`
core path. The test at line 235 is misnamed and doesn\'t actually test ack. We n
eed to replace it with a real test:\n- Establish `MessagesLoaded` with a temp me
